post_text:
Open House - Back to School Days

Check in at your school to take care of paperwork, payments, picking up your child's device, drop off your child's school supplies (elementary only), and get your son/daughter's school picture taken (high school only).

When: August 10th through 12th from 12:00 - 6:00 p.m. as follows:

Monday, August 10 - Green Families
Tuesday, August 11 - Blue Families
Wednesday, August 12 - Green or Blue Families

Need to know what color your family is? Look for the green or blue dot affixed to the outside of the Back to School mailer you received in the mail. Lost your mailer? No problem. Call your child's school and they will tell you your family's color.

We hope to see you all at Open House/Back to School Days.

PS Want to pay online? The convenience fee will be waived from August 10th - August 12th.

Kandiyohi County and the Willmar Economic Development Commission‚Äôs Broadband committee are working on ways to improve the internet in the county.

The survey is at http://kandiyohi.com/broadband-survey/ and asks questions about reliability and use during the pandemic.

Even if you don't live in Kandiyohi County, your information is valuable as they work with companies looking at building the fiber infrastructure.

You are also welcome to reach out to Michelle at 320-287-1737 or Connie at the EDC office (320-235-7370) if you have questions.

post_text:
Since Memorial Day commemorations can not be held in the usual ways this year, instrumentalists of all ages are urged to take part in ‚ÄúTAPS ACROSS AMERICA.‚Äù

Below you will find music for TAPS. Though TAPS is typically played by a trumpet or bugle, everyone is welcome to take part regardless of what instrument you play. I have written out TAPS in 2 different keys--it is usually played in B-flat, however some instruments/performers may find it easier to play the E-flat version.

If you‚Äôd like more information you can visit the website

https://www.tapsforveterans.org/national-moment-of-remembrance/

There you can officially register as a participant and/or post a video of your playing of TAPS.

Even if you don‚Äôt officially register, step out onto your porch, front yard, or driveway at 3:00 PM on Monday and sound TAPS in remembrance of our countries fallen heros.

post_text:
Dear All of MACCRAY,

Just moments ago Governor Walz ordered Distance Learning to continue through the end of this school year.

He recognizes the difficulties to the Class of 2020 of not experiencing commencement, missing prom and not being able to participate in extra-curriculars. He feels the Class of 2020 will long be remembered for their participation in helping to eliminate this disease.

Governor Walz thanked teachers. They are working hard to reach out. They are working to reduce inequities between children and offer all the help they can for our students. Thank you to MACCRAY teachers!

Please know that, at MACCRAY, we will continue to educate our students and reach out to them. Reach out to us if you see a way we can better help you.

We want to help as this new world opens up to us.

With care, and in education, you have my best regards,

Sherri Broderius
Superintendent
